    "outcome": "Australia",
    "explanation": "\n## Executive Summary\nThe Australia vs India Women's ODI Series concluded with Australia emerging victorious. Initially, the market slightly favored Australia, but confidence dipped after India won the preceding T20I series 2-1, leading the market to momentarily favor India. However, the market quickly corrected back to Australia as the ODI series approached, recognizing Australia's historical dominance and World Cup champion status in the 50-over format. Australia then solidified this prediction by emphatically winning the first ODI by six wickets, setting the tone for their eventual series victory.\n\n## Timeline Of Key Events\n- **2026-02-21**: India Women defeat Australia Women to win the T20I series 2-1, causing market confidence to briefly flip in favor of India for the upcoming ODI series ([art_sports_20260221_010_9a54d7da]).\n- **2026-02-22**: Market prediction flips back in favor of Australia as focus shifts to the 50-over format, where Australia are the reigning World Cup champions and historically dominant.\n- **2026-02-24**: Australia Women comprehensively beat India Women by six wickets in the 1st ODI, chasing down India's 214 with ease ([art_sports_20260224_012_b0885cff], [art_sports_20260224_015_dcb9536b]).\n- **2026-02-27**: Australia goes on to win the ODI series.\n\n## Causal Chain Analysis\nThe outcome was primarily driven by Australia's superior ODI pedigree. The brief market flip to India was triggered by India's success in the shorter T20I format ([art_sports_20260221_010_9a54d7da]). However, this optimism for India was short-lived because the 50-over format requires different pacing and endurance, areas where Australia excels. This inherent strength led to a market correction back to Australia. The proximate trigger for Australia's actual series win was their dominant performance in the 1st ODI, where they easily chased down India's total, proving their superiority and ultimately leading to the series victory ([art_sports_20260224_012_b0885cff]).\n\n## Countervailing Factors\nThe main countervailing factor was India's momentum coming into the series after winning the T20I leg 2-1. This gave them psychological confidence and briefly convinced the prediction market of their potential. However, this factor failed because T20I form does not perfectly translate to ODI cricket, and Australia's depth and experience in ODIs overwhelmed India's momentum.\n\n## Event Candidate Inventory\n- **E1: India wins T20I series**\n  - Title: India Women Beat Australia 2-1\n  - Date: 2026-02-21\n  - Why it matters causally: Created false momentum and market hype for India, causing the temporary prediction flip.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_sports_20260221_010_9a54d7da]\n- **E2: Australia wins 1st ODI**\n  - Title: Australia Women vs India Women 1st ODI Result\n  - Date: 2026-02-24\n  - Why it matters causally: Emphatic 6-wicket win set the tone for the series and demoralized the Indian side.\n  - Source article IDs: [art_sports_20260224_012_b0885cff], [art_sports_20260224_015_dcb9536b]\n\n## Evidence Mapping Table\n| Claim/Event | Article IDs | Date Support | Confidence (0-1) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| India won T20I series 2-1 | [art_sports_20260221_010_9a54d7da] | 2026-02-21 | 1.0 | Directly correlates with market shift to 'No' |\n| Australia won 1st ODI by 6 wickets | [art_sports_20260224_012_b0885cff], [art_sports_20260224_015_dcb9536b] | 2026-02-24 | 1.0 | Key step in series victory |\n\n## Uncertainties And Alternative Paths\nThe primary uncertainty was whether India could translate their T20I form into the ODI format. An alternative path would have seen India winning the 1st ODI, which could have derailed Australia's farewell tour for their captain Alyssa Healy and led to an Indian series victory.\n",
